		<h2>Press Release</h2>
		<p>We are excited to announce that on August 5, 2013, DINAMEC SYSTEMS acquired the fluidized bed tool cleaning division of KEPPEL SEGHERS Inc. This included all related assets and the fluidized bed technology, which was formally developed by DINAMEC NV and SEGHERS Better Technology for Services &amp; Machinery Zele NV in Belgium.</p>
		<p>The complete staff of the Keppel Seghers Fluidized Bed Division, remains intact and will continue to serve the needs of our present and future customers, creating a seamless transition.</p>
		<p>DINAMEC SYSTEMS is held by the same individuals who own the company, which has been manufacturing our fluid clean parts since 1995 and building our complete fluidized beds and all the related components since 2005.</p> 
		<p>This alliance will allow us to build on the acquired 25 plus years of “Seghers-Dinamec” experience in fluidized bed parts and tool refurbishing equipment, designing and manufacturing new “Fluid Clean” equipment, while improving our services to the existing former customers of KEPPEL SEGHERS Inc.</p>
		<p>The entire staff of the fluid clean division looks forward to continue working with you, selling new systems, and providing spare parts and maintenance services for your existing <strong>Fluid Clean, Mini Clean, Aluminum Casting Decoring/Heat Treatment Systems</strong> or <strong>Rubber Denuding Systems</strong>.</strong></p>
		<p>For more information or any service you might require please contact us at <strong>1-888-DINAMEC</strong>, or at www.dinamecsystems.com.</p>
